    <p>• Lat­est ev­i­dence – a very low risk of Covid-19 trans­mis­sion through breast milk – is shared with donors and care­givers through e-mails and phone calls.</p>
    <p>• Donors de­tailed their own and fam­ily mem­bers’ his­tory of re­cent travel and ail­ments.</p>
    <p>Health­care pro­fes­sion­als are pro­vided with the lat­est knowl­edge on the safety of PDHM to en­able them to coun­sel fam­i­lies of re­cip­i­ents.</p>
    <p>Courier ser­vices were in­tro­duced in March to trans­port milk to the bank as well as re­cip­i­ents.</p>
    <p>May lead to feed­ing in­tol­er­ance, re­sult­ing in poor weight gain.</p>
    <p>• Three to 10 times higher risk of devel­op­ing necro­tis­ing en­te­ro­col­i­tis, a se­ri­ous in­testi­nal disease and the lead­ing cause of death among pre­ma­ture ba­bies.</p>
    <p>• Up to half of those with the disease die from it.</p>
    <p>The World Health Or­gan­i­sa­tion has en­dorsed the use of donor hu­man milk from a safe source, such as pas­teurised donor hu­man milk, as the first al­ter­na­tive if milk from the bi­o­log­i­cal mother is un­avail­able.</p>


